Heads of security agencies in Kogi State, made up of the Nigeria Army, Navy, Air Force, Police, Civil Defence Corps, and Vigilante services have hailed the passion of the state governor, Yahaya Bello, towards the security of lives of citizens and dwellers in the state. The heads of security agencies made this known on Monday during a Sallah homage to the governor at the Kogi state Government House, Lokoja. Speaking on their behalf, the State Commissioner of Police, Edward Egbuka, noted that the whole country was challenged by various security concerns, but Kogi could boast of an effective security template that other parts of the country could copy. The police commissioner, on behalf of other security chiefs, promised not to rest on their oars and to further improve on the security successes in the confluence state Bello in his response appreciated the eecurity heads for their steadfast work, noting that every person from within and outside the nation has testified that Kogi was significantly different in its security experiences. He noted that the synergy among the security chiefs was rare and that such was the standard required at the national level noting that when he emerged as the President, he would replicate the same. He finally assured that his government would continue to do everything possible to ensure that the people of the state sleep with their two eyes closed. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com